<Author>Eur0peanVacati0n
<Content>Not my favourite Hotel We stayed here for 2 nights with some German friends. The Hotel is very average. I wouldn't reccommend it. It is a long way from the centre of Berlin and a long way from the main tourist attractions. It is about a 5 plus minute walk to the tram stop and then another 30 minutes by tram into Alexanderplatz. We ate dinner at the restaurant and it was OK but the breakfast(included in the room rate) was fairly ordinary. There were a few large groups of school kids staying here and they were very noisy, especially in the middle of the night!! The view from our room was of a disused factory littered with rubbish. I think this Hotel is mainly used by large school groups. I would recommend that if you were visiting Berlin to see the sights, you would be better off to stay closer into the Centre. 
