<Author>RickyC
<Content>Average We just stayed at this hotel with a group of high school students. I have mixed feelings about the hotel.Pros-------Staff is relatively friendly and most speak English fairly well. Restaurant serves decent food. Rooms are fairly spacious.Cons-------Very remote location. Closest public transportation is a 5 minute walk to a tramway, not the subway (U-bahn). Ride to Alexanderplatz is approximately 30 minutes. This is a residential neighborhood so not much to do. There is a small bar/restaurant in the area that is awesome. The hotel is a former dorm, so that's what the rooms look like. Beds are hard as a rock and my back ached every morning. 
