<Content>Enjoyed Though it is a small hotel it is in what was the former East. The hotel was clean the food was goodand for the most part the staff were great, there was one or two that let them down, bar staff being one. I think I know a good wine from a bad wine by now. The hotel is in a resedential area, transportconnections are not far though and no doubt there is an abundance of taxis. Go for coffee and cake its seems to an institution and is great. If you go about Easter time its like Christmas all over again. Loved the German people they couldnt do enough to help. We are planning on going back in the near future. when we were there, there was a few Russian folk about, but they didnt even return my good morning or hi or smile. Thats my aim to have coffee with someone Russian. 
